## Checklist before moving to Day 3 (Order Service)

- [ ] Customer Service: registering a profile with a valid `CUSTOMER`-role `user_id` succeeds; a `RESTAURANT_OWNER` `user_id` is rejected
- [ ] Restaurant Service: registering a restaurant defaults to `PENDING`; admin can move it to `APPROVED`
- [ ] Menu Service: creating a category/item on a `PENDING` restaurant is rejected; works once `APPROVED`
- [ ] `GET /internal/customers/{id}`, `GET /internal/restaurants/{id}`, `GET /internal/items/{itemId}` all work directly (not through the Gateway) — Order Service will Feign-call all three on Day 3
- [ ] Every service's Swagger UI loads and shows both its public and internal endpoints

Day 3–4 (Order Service) will introduce the busiest set of Feign calls yet — to Customer, Restaurant, and Menu Service all at checkout time — using the exact same convention from Section 0.
